coordinate with the concerned officials to revisit existing relief operation system and adopt measures to address the identified gaps to ensure the smooth flow of procedures and regular reporting, to provide information to management and other stakeholders, for decision making and monitoring purposes;

require the GSO/Supply Officer to prepare the Requisition and Issue Slips promptly and summarize the same in the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued to be submitted weekly/monthly to the Municipal Accountant for proper accounting of the supplies issued;

direct the Municipal Accountant to: (i) course through the procurement of goods and supplies to the inventory account and treat the same as an expense once consumed/distributed based on the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) submitted by the Supply Officer; (ii) use logbooks for incoming and outgoing inventories and subsequently be the basis of reporting in the SSMI; and (iii) check the completeness and propriety of supporting documents prescribed under COA Circular No. 2012-001 and other COVID-19 related issuances before processing claims for payments to establish the legality, validity and propriety of the disbursements; and

require the BAC to (i) submit all the originals/authenticated copies of the lacking documents and proper justifications for non-compliance with the provisions of 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 and other COVID-19 related issuances to the Audit Team, thru the Municipal Accountant, to arrive at a decision in audit; and (ii) henceforth, strictly comply with the provisions of the said Revised IRR to establish the validity and regularity of the procurement process and award of contracts/POs and to ensure that information on the funds and their use are reliable, accurate and transparent to enhance accountability of the procurement process.

Direct the Acting Municipal Treasurer to deposit her collections intact and daily to the authorized depository bank on the frequency required under existing regulation;

Direct the Revenue Collectors to remit their collections daily at the close of every business day or the first hour of the following working day to the Liquidating Officer;

Direct all Accountable Officers to prepare Report of Collections and Deposits (RCD) and to record their collections in the Cashbooks on a daily basis; and

Require the Acting Municipal Accountant to maintain Subsidiary Ledgers (SLs) for collections of each Revenue Collectors as well as for Cash Advances.

