We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the Municipal Accountant and the In-Charge of Office (ICO) – Municipal Treasurer to exert extra effort in identifying the accountabilities of each former Municipal Treasurer on the collections that remained undeposited for more than two (2) decades. Upon determination, the Municipal Accountant shall prepare the necessary Journal Entry Vouchers to reclassify the undeposited balance of former Municipal Treasurers from Cash – Local Treasury to a proper Receivable account for fair presentation in the Statement of Financial Position. 

Likewise, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Accountant to:

Make the necessary adjustments for the: (i) noted errors in recording in the Cash – Local Treasury account amounting to P1,040,501.15; (ii) long outstanding cash advances of employees and officers recorded under the Accounts Payable totaling P2,875,102.12; and (iii) reclassification of the Loans Payable – Domestic account from Non-Current Liability to Current Liability for the fair and accurate presentation of the affected accounts in the Statement of Financial Position;

Identify the valid book reconciling items and prepare the necessary adjustments in the Cash in Bank Local Currency Current Account for the fair presentation of the Financial Statements;

Verify the validity and existence of the Accounts Payable and determine whether these are still valid and enforceable especially those that have been dormant for two years or more. After which, notify the concerned payees of their outstanding claims, but, if found to be without valid claim, proper reversion should be made to the Unappropriated Surplus in the General Fund for fair and accurate presentation of the account balances in the financial statements; and

Analyze the unreconciled balances of the Due from and Due to Other Funds account, prepare a reconciliation statement therein and make the necessary adjustments in the books for the affected funds for fair and accurate presentation in the Statement of Financial Position in order to provide information that is reliable and relevant to the users of the Financial Statements.

